         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers0973">
               <p>A native of <placeName>Cornwall</placeName>, Haweis matriculated at Christ Church,
                     <placeName>Oxford</placeName> in <date when="1755">1755</date>, but did not
                  complete a degree. He was ordained as deacon and priest in <date when="1757"
                     >1757</date> by <persName>Thomas Secker</persName>. He served as <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers1341.xml"/>Martin Madan</persName>&apos;s curate at the
                  Lock Chapel, <placeName>London</placeName>, and subsequently as rector of All
                  Saints&apos; church, <placeName>Northampton</placeName>. In later life he was
                  chaplain to Lady <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0964.xml"
                     />Huntingdon</persName> and kept her personal papers. See <hi rend="italic"
                     >Alumni Oxonienses</hi>; <hi rend="italic">DEB</hi>, 536–37; <hi rend="italic"
                     >ODNB</hi>; and Vickers, <hi rend="italic">Dictionary</hi>, 153.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
   </text>
